1. Difference: @Mock vs @MockBean
      @Mock                	@MockBean
      Mockito	              Spring Boot
      Unit test	            Integration test
      No Spring context	    Replaces bean in context
2. @Spy vs @Mock
      @Mock	        @Spy
      Fully fake	  Real + partial mock
3. when() vs doReturn()
      when(obj.method()).thenReturn(val);   // normal
      doReturn(val).when(obj).method();     // for spy
4. Why Mockito needs @ExtendWith? -> To initialize mocks automatically
5. Can Mockito mock private methods? ❌ No (use PowerMockito)
6. Can Mockito mock static methods? ✅ Yes (Mockito 3+)
